<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[828,1437,1579,2083]" lastBlockId="11.[151,760,190,1077]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,944,1579,1603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe not reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites without black spots (
<figureCitation box="[962,1046,1676,1699]" captionStart="Figs 1" captionStartId="2.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,201,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys belenensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177529/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and third rostral segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[879,1046,1739,1763]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1309,1740,1763]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 7A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, bent inwards (
<figureCitation box="[1237,1324,1772,1795]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup trilobate (inner part notched, forming two long, digitiform lobes; outer part tapering), almost straight, elongated, parallel to dorsal rim, and almost reaching posterolateral angle (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1262,1900,1923]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 7A,C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe narrow and triangular, directed to base of proctiger; lateral lobe large, triangular and straight (
<figureCitation box="[835,948,1996,2019]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 7C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with narrow tufts of setae on lateral excavation; posterior face triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1341,2028,2051]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 7C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions developed, distally rounded, vent- rolateral side broadly excavated, dorsal side with brown spot; clearly surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[202,390,253,277]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation box="[551,631,254,277]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin with posterolateral angles dentiform and posteriorly directed, inner angles blunt and not projected; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angles reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; inner margin not projected posteriorly; excavation V-shaped. Valvulae 8 barely exposed. Apices of laterotergites 8 slightly above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 passing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices slightly above imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
