<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,410,765,789]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
For the males, see differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[286,391,798,821]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amyoti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[286,391,798,821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. amyoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[397,479,798,821]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belenensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. belenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[270,356,830,853]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[367,496,830,853]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favachae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[367,496,830,853]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. favachae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[504,588,830,853]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[640,760,830,853]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servillei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[640,760,830,853]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. servillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,234,862,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
due to posterior margin of valvifers 8 concave or slanting, and never reaching posterior margin of valvifers 9. But 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[224,389,926,949]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspilogaster" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[224,389,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. aspilogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[396,480,926,949]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated by inner angle of posterior margin blunt, not dentiform like in the other species and by central excavation V- and not U-shaped like in the other species. The species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[613,760,1022,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belenensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[613,760,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. belenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,234,1054,1077]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the apices of abdominal segment VII clearly below the level of the apices of laterotergites 8 and almost level with the apices of laterotergites 9, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspilogaster" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. aspilogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[921,1006,254,277]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1015,1143,254,277]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favachae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1015,1143,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. favachae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1150,1232,254,277]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1282,1400,254,277]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servillei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1282,1400,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. servillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have the apices of abdominal segment VII almost level with the apices of laterotergites 8 and clearly above the level of laterotergites 9. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1271,1399,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favachae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1271,1399,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. favachae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1011,1129,382,405]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servillei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1011,1129,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">H. servillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1135,1217,382,405]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the distal spine of laterotergites 8 a little bit narrower at base; and margin of valvifers 8 dark.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="300" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[828,1437,190,597]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,956,478,502]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the absence of contrasting black spots on ventral side of the body (Gr. 
<emphasis box="[1230,1306,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">aspilos</emphasis>
, spotless).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
